Test 1 - Portfolio Summary Without Any Crypto Data
    1. Run database_installer
    2. Run the main app
    3. Either create new profile or select existing user
    4. Press login button
    5. Go straight to Check Portfolio Value Screen without added any cryptocurrencies
    6. Click the View Portfolio Summary button
    7. Error raised, "Initial Investment Amount Not Found"

Test 2 - Portfolio Pie Chart Without Any Crypto Data
    1. Run database_installer
    2. Run the main app
    3. Either create new profile or select existing user
    4. Press login button
    5. Go straight to Check Portfolio Value Screen without added any cryptocurrencies
    6. Click the View Portfolio Pie Chart button
    7. No Image will be displayed on Portfolio Entry Values
    8. Message displayed, "Portfolio char loaded successfully"

Test 3 - Specific Entry Without Any Crypto Data
    1. Run database_installer
    2. Run the main app
    3. Either create new profile or select existing user
    4. Press login button
    5. Go straight to Check Portfolio Value Screen without added any cryptocurrencies
    6. Click the Select Specific Entry button
    7. Button is disabled, doesn't do anything

Test 4 - View Portfolio Summary with Crypto Data
    1. Run database_installer
    2. Run the main app
    3. Either create new profile or select existing user
    4. Press login button
    5. Go to the New Portfolio Entry screen and add a crypto to your portfolio (i.e. tether)
    6. Go to the Check Portfolio Value screen
    7. Click the View Portfolio Summary button
    8. Displays: investment amount, current portfolio value, and portfolio value change
    9. Message displayed, "Portfolio Entry Displayed"

Test 5 - View Portfolio Pie Chart with Crypto Data
    1. Run database_installer
    2. Run the main app
    3. Either create new profile or select existing user
    4. Press login button
    5. Go to the New Portfolio Entry screen and add a crypto to your portfolio (i.e. tether)
    6. Go to the Check Portfolio Value screen
    7. Click the View Portfolio Pie Chart button
    8. Displays pie chart of your portfolio entry or entries
    9. Message displayed, "Portfolio chart loaded successfully"

Test 6 - View a Specific Entry with Crypto Data
    1. Run database_installer
    2. Run the main app
    3. Either create new profile or select existing user
    4. Press login button
    5. Go to the New Portfolio Entry screen and add a crypto to your portfolio (i.e. tether)
    6. Go to the Check Portfolio Value screen
    7. Click the Select Specific Entry spinner
    8. CLick on one of your entries (entries are in numerical order by when you added them to your portfolio)
    9. Once the input is received, the app will display the investment amount, current portfolio value,
       and portfolio value change of the selected cryptocurrency
    10. Message displayed: "Portfolio Entry Displayed"


